Schwendiman is a surname from Switzerland meaning stub up / clear land and forest. It is from the Siss German dialect.

The Schwendiman family crest consists of a lion between the firs representing the hard work a Swiss woodsman did in the early days. 

Schwendi in high german is called: Schwenten. 

Noteable Schwendimans include:

Blake Schwendiman: American author
Stephen Schwendiman: Assistant Utah Attorney General
Jeremy C. Schwendiman: America author